	(19685, 19, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Such is their animosity that they vie for the honor of being sent to assist the naaru there. Each day, that decision is made here by A\'dal. The armies gather here to receive A\'dal\'s blessing before heading to Shadowmoon.'),
	(19685, 18, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'There he continues to wage war on Illidan with the assistance of the Aldor and the Scryers. The two factions have not given up on their old feuds, though.'),
	(19685, 17, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The attacks against Shattrath continued, but the city did not fall, as you can see. On the contrary, the naaru known as Xi\'ri led a successful incursion into Shadowmoon Valley - Illidan\'s doorstep.'),
	(19685, 16, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Aldor\'s most holy temple and its surrounding dwellings lie on the terrace above. As a holy site, only the initiated are welcome inside.'),
	(19685, 15, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Many of the priesthood had been slain by the same magisters who now vowed to serve the naaru. They were not happy to share the city with their former enemies.'),
	(19685, 14, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Aldor are followers of the Light and forgiveness and redemption are values they understand. However, they found hard to forget the deeds of the blood elves while under Kael\'s command.'),
	(19685, 13, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The naaru accepted the defectors, who would become known as the Scryers; their dwelling lies in the platform above. Only those initiated with the Scryers are allowed there.'),
	(19685, 12, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The defection of Voren\'thal and his followers was the largest loss ever incurred by Kael\'s forces. And these weren\'t just any blood elves. Many of the best and brightest amongst Kael\'s scholars and magisters had been swayed by Voren\'thal\'s influence.'),
	(19685, 11, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'As the naaru approached him, Voren\'thal kneeled before him and uttered the following words: "I\'ve seen you in a vision, naaru. My race\'s only hope for survival lies with you. My followers and I are here to serve you."'),
	(19685, 9, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'As the regiment of blood elves crossed this very bridge, the Aldor\'s exarchs and vindicators lined up to defend the Terrace of Light. But then the unexpected happened.'),
	(19685, 10, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The blood elves laid down their weapons in front of the city\'s defenders; their leader, a blood elf elder known as Voren\'thal, stormed into the Terrace of Light and demanded to speak to A\'dal.'),
	(19685, 8, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'It wouldn\'t be long, however, before the city came under attack once again. This time, the attack came from Illidan\'s armies. A large regiment of blood elves had been sent by Illidan\'s ally, Kael\'thas Sunstrider, to lay waste to the city.'),
	(19685, 7, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The priesthood, known as the Aldor, quickly regained its strength as word spread that the naaru had returned and reconstruction soon began. The ruined temple is now used as an infirmary for injured refugees.'),
	(19685, 6, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'They were drawn to the ruins of Shattrath City where a small remnant of the draenei priesthood conducted its rites inside a ruined temple on this very spot.'),
	(19685, 5, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Sha\'tar, or "born from light" are the naaru that came to Outland to fight the demons of the Burning Legion.'),
	(19685, 4, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Let us go into the Lower City. I will warn you that as one of the only safe havens in Outland, Shattrath has attracted droves of refugees from all wars, current and past.'),
